Merry CHRISTmas to all of my friends and family! I hope y’all have a blessed day and that we all remember the true reason for the season.

Thanks to Gab for throwing Sasha her first birthday party tonight. 🐾🎉🥳 It’s hard to believe she’s fourteen years old. Sasha joined our family when Gabby was in kindergarten and they literally grew up together. She’s been the best dog one could ask for. We sure do love this old girl! #pitbull #birthdaygirl #bestdogever #pitbullsofinstagram

Twenty years ago on a cold and snowy morning, the Lord blessed me with the greatest gift of my life: a healthy, happy baby girl. A that moment, my life was greatly changed. It was no longer about me. It was all about her and bettering myself to give her the life she deserved. She became my reason for being, my motivation to be better. As the saying goes, I may have given her life, but she gave me the reason to live. Life wasn’t the easiest and she and I have grown up together over the years, and she has grown into one of the most resilient, caring, beautiful, loving, and intelligent young ladies I’ve ever known. She’s an old soul, wise beyond her years and if you know her, you can agree with me on that. I thank God for her daily and I pray the she knows just how much she’s loved, just how special she is to so many people, and that she has the ability to do whatever she puts her mind to. I pray that the Lord will continue to keep her and protect her and guide her through life. 
Happy birthday, Gabby. I love you more than words can ever express! 
#mybaby #aquariusseason

The @fishersofkidsanglersacademy & @greene.county4h’s Minnows Fishing Camp was a success! So thankful for a fun and safe day with the littles. Looking forward to fishing with the bigger kids tomorrow. Huge thanks to the Pridgen’s for allowing us to hold these camps there again this summer. Thanks to all the adults/volunteers that were there today. This wouldn’t be possible without the help of so many others.
If you don’t see your child in the pictures, don’t worry. I am still waiting for pictures from some of their fishing buddies. I will add them to this post once I get them.
*We still need a few more volunteers to help tomorrow. If you can help, please let me know. Thanks!
#takeakidfishing #zebcofishing #lewsfishing #ratheroutdoors #PridgenPond #pondsideministries

The @fishersofkidsanglersacademy & @greene.county4h’s Hook, Line, & Sinker fishing camp was a success. We had such a great time fishing with the older kids yesterday. I’m so thankful for everyone that helped make this day possible. Thank you, again and again, to the Pridgen’s for allowing us to fish at their pond another year. Huge thanks to @zebcofishing for sending rod & reel combos for all the kids to use and take home so they can continue to grow as fishermen. Thanks to Greene County 4-H for another opportunity to share the love of fishing with our youth. 

Our next camp will be held the morning of Friday, July 14, at Cutter Creek Golf Club. Don’t forget to sign your child up at www.fishersofkidsanglersacademy.org. Volunteers can also register to help on the website, as well. Our final summer camp will be held in partnership with the Edgecombe County 4-H & Livestock in Tarboro, NC, on July 25. Details on how to register for that camp are also on my website. Thanks again to all who made this day possible!! I am truly grateful and can never fully express how much it means to me and the kids. #takeakidfishing #ratheroutdoors #zebcofishing #pridgenpond #pondsideministries

I told myself I wasn’t going to do this, mainly because I couldn’t bare to look through the many photos and videos of my sweet Sasha. It’s been seventy-two hours since we said our final goodbyes. I still find myself looking for her to greet me at the door after work or lay her head on my pillow at night. Sasha came into our lives in February of 2009 when Gabby was only six years old and has been a huge part of our lives ever since. Those two practically grew up together. Making the decision to let her go was one of the hardest decisions we’ve ever had to make. She fought a good fight and would have continued to do so, if she’d been able. She was such a good girl and we will miss her forever. #ripsasha #bestdogever

social_posts.post_text: Well, we got rained out today after a huge thunderstorm rolled in this morning and had to call the #CATCH42 Memorial Fishing Camp early. We didn’t let that ruin our whole day though. Before leaving, volunteers and participants picked up their @zebcofishing rod, @theikefoundation @flambeau_outdoors tackle boxes, with @hiseasfishingline, @strikekinglurecompany and @ragetail soft plastic baits, @zmanfishingproducts chatter baits and trds, and @livingstonlures Dive Master Jr. A few folks hung around and about 11:00 we finally got the chance to fish for a few hours and made the best of our day as we could. Thanks to everyone who came out to help and fish. Hopefully, we will get a chance to do this again. Be share to swipe all the way to the end to see who joined us on the water for a little while. #takeakidfishing #firstcatch #bassfishing #golfcourseponds #catchphotorelease

Senior year loading 🏴‍☠️🎓 Only five classes remaining until Gab graduates with a Bachelor of Arts in Psychology. She then plans to pursue a Master’s degree in Marriage and Family Counseling and become a therapist/counselor for at-risk youth. She’s counseled friends her entire life and I know she will make a huge difference in the lives of those she works with in the future. 
Words cannot even begin to express how proud I am of my baby girl. She’s driven and extremely intelligent, not to mention gorgeous, inside and out, with a kind heart and a good head on her shoulders. There’s nothing she can’t do when she puts her mind to it and I pray she has a safe and successful year. #eastcarolinauniversity #pirates #senior #classof2024 #psychology #undergraduate #mybabygirl #proudmamamoment

Looks like I’ve still got it. I’ve spent the past four months gardening with my dad, working on my #greenthumb more than my #bassthumb. Spending that time with my him has been good for my soul. It’s hard to believe it’s already been five years since I caught my #personalbest #largemouthbass. This beautiful beast weighed 7-pounds 14-ounces and was almost 26 inches long. It was all I could do to contain my emotions and adrenaline  enough to get some pictures with her before releasing her back into the pond. What I would give to get my hands on one like her soon. It’s definitely over due! #airrusrods #lewsfishing #hiseas #strikeking #ragetail #ragecraw #bucketmouth #catchandrelease #fishlikeagirl
Grateful today and every day for this girl. She is and always has been my reason for being. Love you, Gabs! #nationaldaughtersday #myheart #mybabygirl

I went fishing after work today #inmemory of my late grandma. It’s hard to believe it’s already been four years since we lost this special lady, the person most responsible for influencing my love of fishing. My grandma knew the healing powers of fishing and made sure to share them with her family. There isn’t a day that goes by or a cast that is made that I don’t think of her. You can best believe her legacy lives on through me and every child that I teach to fish. 💕🎣 #ripgrandma #family #fishing #bassfishing #airrusrods #lewsfishing #hiseas #bassfishing #catchandrelease #pondfishing

A quick twenty-four hour #saltwaterfishing trip with a good buddy of mine turned out to be an adventure that I will never forget. Last night, we went trout fishing until 2:00 in the morning and ended up catching several #reddrum and my new #personalbest #stripedbass, in the process. This morning, we caught #bluefish to use as bait for #bluefintuna fishing and I got to experience the excitement of getting that big bite while hearing that drag whine briefly before realizing the fish just  snatched our bait off the hook. After the sharks finished off the rest of our bait, we decided to start heading back inland and continued fishing for red drum and speckled trout. Not only  did I make a new canine friend, am I also bringing back a cooler full of fish for my dad. I had such a great time and I’m looking forward to next chance I get to do this again. #fishing #saltwatertherapy #troutfishing #drumfishing #striper #catchandrelease #fishmonkeygloves #gillfishing #carhartt
